==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chlamyphore
<hw>Chlam"y*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ cloak +
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small South
American edentate (<spn>Chlamyphorus truncatus</spn>, and
<spn>Chlamyphorus retusus</spn>) allied to the armadillo. It is covered
with a leathery shell or coat of mail, like a cloak, attached along the
spine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chlamys</ent>⟦br⟧
